  "prompt": "What are the penalties for money laundering under federal law?",
  "response": "Under federal law, money laundering is a serious criminal offense with significant penalties. Generally, penalties can include:\n\n1. Criminal Penalties:\n- Fines up to $500,000 or double the value of the property involved\n- Prison sentences up to 20 years\n- Potential asset forfeiture\n\n2. Specific Statute Details:\n- 18 U.S. Code \u00a7 1956 covers money laundering criminal offenses\n- Penalties vary based on specific circumstances and amount of money involved\n\n3. Additional Consequences:\n- Criminal record\n- Loss of professional licenses\n- Potential civil penalties\n- Potential deportation for non-citizens\n\nThe exact penalties depend on specific factors like transaction amount, intent, and whether it involves international or domestic transactions. Consulting a legal professional would provide the most accurate details for a specific situation.",
